ating to Japanese Americans in the aftermath of their wartime confinement, including resettlement nationwide, the mental and physical readjustment of the former inmates, and their political engagement, most notably in concert with other racialized and ethnic minority groups.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCold WarxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aCommunity lifezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aJapanese AmericansxCivil rightsxHistoryy20th century. 0aJapanese AmericansxForced removal and internment, 1942-1945. 0aJapanese AmericansxPolitics and governmenty20th century. 0aJapanese AmericansxSocial conditionsy20th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095227040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520952270423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520952270/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles